{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-adj}}\n\n# [[funny]], [[amusing]]\n#: {{syn|fr|comique|désopilant|marrant|[[rigolo]] {{q|informal}}|[[poilant]] {{q|France|informal}}|[[crampant]] {{q|Quebec|informal}}|[[fendard]] {{q|France|slang}}}}\n#: {{ux|fr|On a beaucoup ri, il est vraiment très '''drôle'''.|t=We laughed a lot, he was really so '''funny'''.}}\n# {{lb|fr|sometimes with \"de\"}} [[strange]], [[weird]], [[bizarre]]\n#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1882|author=Guy de Maupassant|title=Madame Baptiste\n|passage=C’est '''drôle''', mais c’est comme ça...|t=It's '''weird''', but that's how it is...}}\n#* {{quote-book|fr|year=1901|author=Adolphe Orain|title=Contes de l’Ille-et-Vilaine|page=207\n|passage=C’était un bien '''drôle de''' petit homme que le père Langevin, tailleur et porteur de contraintes au Grand-Fougeray.|t=He was quite an '''odd''' little man, that Father Langevin, mason and \"porteur de contraintes\" in {{w|Grand-Fougeray}}}}\n#* {{quote-song|fr|year=1977|artist={{w|Michel Sardou}}|title=Dix ans plus tôt|passage=Tu voulais m'épouser, quelle '''drôle''' d'idée, tu n'avais pas 15 ans|t=You wanted to marry me, what an '''odd''' idea, you were only fifteen}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|fr\n|drolatique\n|drôle de guerre\n|drôlement\n|drôlerie}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|lou|drol|dròl}}\n* {{desc|en|droll|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|eo|drola|der=1}}\n\n","alt":[],"syn":["comique","désopilant","marrant","[[rigolo]] {{q|informal}}","informal","[[poilant]] {{q|France|informal}}","France","informal","[[crampant]] {{q|Quebec|informal}}","Quebec","informal","[[fendard]] {{q|France|slang}}","France","slang"],"type":"adj","forms":[{"g":"m","n":"s"},{"g":"f","n":"s"}],"preps":[{"rel":"adj","prep":"à","ex":"histoire drôle à entendre"},{"rel":"adj","prep":"de","ex":"avoir une drôle d’idée"}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">drôle</strong> (<i>plural</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr p-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4les#French\" title=\"drôles\">drôles</a></b>)</span>\n</p><ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/funny\" title=\"funny\">funny</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/amusing\" title=\"amusing\">amusing</a>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"nyms synonym\"><span class=\"defdate\">Synonyms:</span> <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/comique#French\" title=\"comique\">comique</a></span>; <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/d%C3%A9sopilant#French\" title=\"désopilant\">désopilant</a></span>; <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/marrant#French\" title=\"marrant\">marrant</a></span>; <a href=\"/wiki/rigolo\" title=\"rigolo\">rigolo</a> <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">informal</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/poilant\" title=\"poilant\">poilant</a> <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">France<span class=\"ib-comma qualifier-comma\">,</span> informal</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span>; <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=crampant&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"crampant (page does not exist)\">crampant</a> <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">Quebec<span class=\"ib-comma qualifier-comma\">,</span> informal</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/fendard\" title=\"fendard\">fendard</a> <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">France<span class=\"ib-comma qualifier-comma\">,</span> slang</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span></span></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">On a beaucoup ri, il est vraiment très <b>drôle</b>.</i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">We laughed a lot, he was really so <b>funny</b>.</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"usage-label-sense\"><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content label-content\">sometimes with \"de\"</span><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">)</span></span> <a href=\"/wiki/strange\" title=\"strange\">strange</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/weird\" title=\"weird\">weird</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/bizarre\" title=\"bizarre\">bizarre</a>\n<ul><li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1882</b></span>, Guy de Maupassant, <cite>Madame Baptiste</cite>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">C’est <b>drôle</b>, mais c’est comme ça...</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">It's <b>weird</b>, but that's how it is...</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li>\n<li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1901</b></span>, Adolphe Orain, <cite>Contes de l’Ille-et-Vilaine</cite>, page <span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\">207</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">C’était un bien <b>drôle de</b> petit homme que le père Langevin, tailleur et porteur de contraintes au Grand-Fougeray.</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">He was quite an <b>odd</b> little man, that Father Langevin, mason and \"porteur de contraintes\" in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand-Fougeray\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Grand-Fougeray\">Grand-Fougeray</a></span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li>\n<li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1977</b></span>, “Dix ans plus tôt”, performed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michel_Sardou\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Michel Sardou\">Michel Sardou</a>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">Tu voulais m'épouser, quelle <b>drôle</b> d'idée, tu n'avais pas 15 ans</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">You wanted to marry me, what an <b>odd</b> idea, you were only fifteen</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li></ol><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Derived_terms\">Derived terms</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=dr%C3%B4le&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Derived terms\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><div class=\"list-switcher-wrapper\"><div class=\"term-list columns-bg\"><ul><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/drolatique#French\" title=\"drolatique\">drolatique</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4le_de_guerre#French\" title=\"drôle de guerre\">drôle de guerre</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4lement#French\" title=\"drôlement\">drôlement</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4lerie#French\" title=\"drôlerie\">drôlerie</a></span></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Descendants\">Descendants</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=dr%C3%B4le&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Descendants\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><ul><li>Louisiana Creole: <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"lou\"><a href=\"/wiki/drol#Louisiana_Creole\" title=\"drol\">drol</a></span>, <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"lou\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B2l#Louisiana_Creole\" title=\"dròl\">dròl</a></span><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r68481116\">.mw-parser-output .desc-arr[title]{cursor:help}.mw-parser-output .desc-arr[title=\"uncertain\"]{font-size:.7em;vertical-align:super}</style></li>\n<li><span class=\"desc-arr\" title=\"borrowed\">→</span> English: <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"en\"><a href=\"/wiki/droll#English\" title=\"droll\">droll</a></span><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r68481116\"></li>\n<li><span class=\"desc-arr\" title=\"reshaped by analogy or addition of morphemes\">⇒</span> Esperanto: <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"eo\"><a href=\"/wiki/drola#Esperanto\" title=\"drola\">drola</a></span><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r68481116\"></li></ul>","trans":["funny, amusing","strange, weird, bizarre"]},{"section":"\n{{fr-noun|m|f=drôlesse|f2=drôlière}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|archaic}} [[rascal]], [[scoundrel]]\n#* {{quote-book|fr|title=La Reine Margot|year=1845|author={{w|Alexandre Dumas}}|text={{...}}et puis, je me suis un peu détourné de la ligne droite pour aller jeter à la rivière un affreux enfant qui criait : À bas les papistes, vive l’amiral ! Malheureusement, je crois que le '''drôle''' savait nager.|t={{...}}and then, I went a little off the straight part of the road to hurl a repulsive child who was shouting \"Down with the papists, long live the admiral!\" into the river. Unfortunately, I believe that the '''rascal''' could swim.}}\n# {{lb|fr|southern France|endearing}} [[child]], [[kid]], [[lad]]\n#* {{quote-book|fr|title=Un adolescent d’autrefois|author=François Mauriac|year=1969|publisher=Flammarion|page=284|text=Qu’est-ce que tu en sais, mon pauvre '''drôle''' ?|t=What do you know about it, my poor little '''thing'''?}}\n\n","alt":[],"syn":[],"type":"noun","forms":[{"g":"m","n":"s"}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">drôle</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"gender\"><abbr title=\"masculine gender\">m</abbr></span> (<i>plural</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr p-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4les#French\" title=\"drôles\">drôles</a></b>, <i>feminine</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr f-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dr%C3%B4lesse#French\" title=\"drôlesse\">drôlesse</a></b> <i>or</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr f-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=dr%C3%B4li%C3%A8re&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"drôlière (page does not exist)\">drôlière</a></b>)</span>\n</p><ol><li><span class=\"usage-label-sense\"><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content label-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#archaic\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">archaic</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">)</span></span> <a href=\"/wiki/rascal\" title=\"rascal\">rascal</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/scoundrel\" title=\"scoundrel\">scoundrel</a>\n<ul><li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1845</b></span>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexandre_Dumas\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Alexandre Dumas\">Alexandre Dumas</a>, <cite>La Reine Margot</cite>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\"><span class=\"q-hellip-sp\"></span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\">[</span>…<span class=\"q-hellip-b\">]</span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\"> </span>et puis, je me suis un peu détourné de la ligne droite pour aller jeter à la rivière un affreux enfant qui criait : À bas les papistes, vive l’amiral ! Malheureusement, je crois que le <b>drôle</b> savait nager.</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\"><span class=\"q-hellip-sp\"> </span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\">[</span>…<span class=\"q-hellip-b\">]</span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\"> </span>and then, I went a little off the straight part of the road to hurl a repulsive child who was shouting \"Down with the papists, long live the admiral!\" into the river. Unfortunately, I believe that the <b>rascal</b> could swim.</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>\n<li><span class=\"usage-label-sense\"><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content label-content\">southern France<span class=\"ib-comma label-comma\">,</span> <a href=\"/wiki/endearing\" title=\"endearing\">endearing</a></s